quran[10]{c,v,t,f}:
  47,20,"And those who have attained faith say, “If only a surah{1}was sent down.” Yet when a decisive surah is sent down and combat is mentioned in it, you<a class=""sup""><sup>sg </sup></a>see those in whose hearts is sickness looking at you with the look of someone fainting at death. Yet worthier of them would be",footnotes:1:<sup></sup>Each portion of the Qur'an is called a ‘surah’, which is sometimes translated as ‘chapter’.Each portion of the Qur'an is called a ‘surah’, which is sometimes translated as ‘chapter’.
  47,21,"obedience and upright speech. Then, when the matter is settled, had they been true to Allah, it would have been better for them."
  47,22,"Would you<a class=""sup""><sup>pl </sup></a>then, in case <span class="h">you became in charge{1}</span>, spread corruption in the earth and <span class="h">sever{2}</span>your family ties{3}?",footnotes:1:[<span class="qiraat-footnote">Qira’at: Roways read it as: “…in case you were made in charge, spread corruption…”</span>],footnotes:2:[<span class="qiraat-footnote">Qira’at: Ya’qub read it as: “…and cut your family ties?</span>],footnotes:3:[Literally “sever your wombs”.]
  47,23,"Those are the ones whom Allah has cursed, so He made them deaf and blinded their sight<i class=""s"">(s) </i>{1}.",footnotes:1:Mentioned in plural form in Arabic, denoted by (s) in English for grammatical reasons.
  47,24,"Will they not ponder the Recital{1}, or are there locks upon their hearts?",footnotes:1:The Arabic word used is Qur’anwhich literally means recital or recitation.
  47,25,"Indeed, those who turned on their heels after guidance became evident to them—Satan has enticed <span class=""h"">them</span><span class="h">and has filled{1}</span><span class=""h"">them</span>with false hopes.",footnotes:1:<span class="qiraat-footnote">Qira’at: Abu Amr read it as: “Satan has enticed them. Thus they were filled with false hopes.” Ya’qub read it as: “Satan has enticed them. Thus I filled them with false hopes.”</span>
  47,26,"That is because they said to those who hated what Allah had bestowed from on high, “We will obey you in certain matters.” But Allah knows their <span class="h">secret exchanges{1}</span>.",footnotes:1:<span class="qiraat-footnote">Qira’at: All except for Hafs, Hamza, Al-Kesa’i and Khalaf read it as: “…their secrets.”</span>
  47,27,"How will it be when the angels take them at death, beating their faces and their backs?"
  47,28,"That is because they followed what angered Allah, and they disliked His good pleasure, so He nullified their deeds."
  47,29,"Or did those in whose hearts is sickness think that Allah would not bring out<i class=""s"">(to the open) </i>their malice?"
